Cluster --------


kubectl config current-context ---> Check Which Cluster You're Connected.

kubectl config get-contexts -->  View All Cluster Contexts (If Multiple)

kubectl cluster-info --> Check Cluster Info


Namespace ----------------


kubectl get all -n <namespace>

kubectl get namespaces --> List All Namespaces in the Cluster

kubectl get all -n <kube-system>


POD  --------------------

kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n <namespace> -- /bin/sh
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n <namespace> -- /bin/bash


kubectl get pods -n <namespace>

kubectl get pods -n <namespace>

kubectl get pods -l app=<pod name>



